DOC.brief_summary: The purpose of this study is to evaluate how taking duloxetine 60mg every day affects the transfer of two normal body chemicals, 3,4-dihydroxyphenylglycol (DHPG) and norepinephrine (NE), across cells in blood and cerebrospinal fluid.
DOC.brief_title: Evaluation of the Effects of Duloxetine on Norepinephrine
DOC.criteria: Healthy subjects between the ages of 1865 years are nonsmokers or are willing to refrain from smoking and are not taking concomitant medications which may inhibit or induce CYP1A2 or CYPD6 or is an MAOI.
